<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06200143 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06200143 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  MOUNTAIN-VIEW; STORE; MAN; ASSAULT; VICTIM; SURGERY; REPORT  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  An 80-year-old Mountain View neighborhood store owner was pistol-whipped by awould-be robber late Tuesday night and underwent surgery Wednesday.;    HazaraLalli came up behind the robber while he was waiting for Lalli's son to takemoney from the cash register at their store, Frenchie's Market on El CaminoReal.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  STORE OWNER, 80, PISTOL-WHIPPED  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The robber turned and hit Lalli in the face with a handgun, cutting him andbreaking several bones, police said. Lalli had not known the robbery wastaking place, officers said.;    After striking Lalli, the gunman left thestore, but as he turned to go out, a friend of Lalli's came from another partof the store and the robber struck him in the stomach, again using the gun,police said.;    The assailant was described as black, in his late teens orearly 20s. An accomplice, described as a Hispanic teen-ager, had waitedoutside the store and the two ran off.;    Witnesses told police they saw thetwo get into a red, four-door sedan.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff Report  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Peninsula/AM  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910718  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  170  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday July 18, 199100200143,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>